Questions:
Which of the following is considered the experimental component of the Pilot Randomized Study of a Proactive Financial Navigation Intervention in Patients With Newly Diagnosed Gastric and Gastroesophageal Junction (GEJ) Adenocarcinoma?
A) Completing surveys about financial experiences and quality of life;
B) Review of medical records by the research study team;
C) Participation in monthly phone calls with community-based partners for financial navigation assistance;
D) Watching a series of online videos about financial literacy and healthcare coverage.

Correct answer: C

What alternative options are available to participants who choose not to enroll in the financial navigation program of the study?
A) Participants can seek financial advice from independent financial advisors; 
B) Participants will not have any alternative options and must manage their finances without assistance;
C) Participants can access financial programs offered by their community or where they receive their cancer treatment;
D) Participants are required to find their own resources without any guidance from the study team.

Correct answer: C

If you have concerns or questions about your rights as a participant in the study, whom should you contact?

A) The principal investigator of the study; 
B) The Director of the Fred Hutch Institutional Review Office;
C) Your personal physician;
D) The National Comprehensive Cancer Network (NCCN).

Correct answer: B) The Director of the Fred Hutch Institutional Review Office
